    </div>

    <p>Whether you follow a vegan diet, have gelatin allergies, or simply want cleaner candy with fewer synthetic ingredients, this guide covers every price point and flavor profile. We also have dedicated deep-dives into specific subcategories: <a href="/candy/vegan-gummy-bears/">vegan gummy bears</a>, <a href="/candy/organic-gummy-bears/">organic gummy bears</a>, <a href="/candy/vegan-gummy-worms/">vegan gummy worms</a>, <a href="/candy/plant-based-gummy-candy/">plant-based gummy candy</a>, <a href="/candy/best-sour-gummies/">best sour gummies</a>, <a href="/candy/best-swedish-gummies/">best Swedish gummies</a>, and <a href="/candy/best-japanese-gummies/">best Japanese gummies</a>.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Candy, not vitamins.</strong> This guide covers vegan gummy candy — the stuff you eat for enjoyment. Looking for vegan gummy vitamins instead? See our <a href="/vegan-gummies/">best vegan gummies guide</a> for plant-based supplements including multivitamins, sleep gummies, and more.
    </div>

    <!-- WHAT TO LOOK FOR -->
    <h2>What Makes Great Vegan Gummy Candy</h2>

    <p>Not all gelatin-free candy is created equal. The best vegan gummy candy nails four criteria: gelling agent quality, flavor authenticity, sugar profile, and ingredient transparency. Here is what separates the elite products from the mediocre ones.</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="leaf" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>Pectin vs Gelatin</h4>
        <p>Pectin, derived from citrus peel or apple pomace, creates a slightly softer chew than gelatin. Modern formulations combine pectin with tapioca starch for a texture nearly identical to conventional gummies. Agar-agar from seaweed is used less frequently but produces a firmer bite.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="star" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>Flavor Authenticity</h4>
        <p>The best brands use real fruit juice concentrates and natural flavors instead of artificial flavoring. This produces a more complex, less synthetic taste. YumEarth and Surf Sweets lead here with organic fruit juice as primary flavor sources.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="scale" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>Sugar Content</h4>
        <p>Traditional gummy bears pack 34g of sugar per bag. SmartSweets cut that to 3g using allulose and stevia. Mid-range brands like YumEarth use organic cane sugar at moderate levels. Decide which matters more: zero sugar or natural sweetness.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="shield" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>Certifications</h4>
        <p>Vegan Society, Certified Vegan, USDA Organic, Non-GMO Project Verified, and Certified Gluten-Free are the gold-standard marks. These require third-party auditing of ingredients and supply chains, not just marketing claims.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

