    <h3>Why SmartSweets Gummy Bears Are Our Top Pick</h3>

    <p>SmartSweets single-handedly created the low-sugar gummy candy category and remains the dominant player. Their gummy bears deliver a satisfying candy experience with just 3 grams of sugar per bag — compared to 34 grams in a standard Haribo bag. The trick is allulose, a rare sugar that tastes like regular sugar but is absorbed differently by the body, contributing minimal calories. Combined with stevia leaf extract and a pectin-based gelling system, the result is a gummy bear that satisfies candy cravings without the sugar crash.</p>

    <p>In our testing, SmartSweets ranked highest for repeat purchase intent — the metric that matters most. People who try them tend to buy them again, which speaks to genuine satisfaction rather than novelty. The six flavors (raspberry, lemon, apple, peach, pineapple, and orange) are distinct and recognizable, not the generic "fruit" taste common in sugar-free candy. For a deeper dive into the gummy bear subcategory, see our <a href="/candy/vegan-gummy-bears/">vegan gummy bears</a> comparison.</p>

