    <p>YumEarth dominates the organic vegan candy space with a simple formula: USDA Organic certification, real fruit juice, and price points that compete with conventional candy. Their gummy bears use organic pectin with colors derived entirely from real food — turmeric for yellow, carrot for orange, purple sweet potato for purple. There are no synthetic dyes, no artificial flavors, and no ingredients you cannot pronounce. The trade-off is sugar: at 14g per bag, these are not low-sugar candy, but the sugar comes from organic cane sugar rather than high-fructose corn syrup. For parents, this is often the decisive factor — clean ingredients matter more than sugar grams when the alternative is Haribo loaded with artificial colors and gelatin. See our full <a href="/candy/organic-gummy-bears/">organic gummy bears</a> roundup for more options in this category.</p>

