    <!-- GELATIN CHECK -->
    <h2>How to Identify Gelatin-Free Gummy Candy</h2>

    <p>Not every gummy candy that looks plant-based actually is. Gelatin hides in surprising places, and marketing terms like "natural" or "fruit-flavored" do not guarantee vegan formulation. Here is a systematic approach to verifying any gummy candy before you buy.</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="search" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>Check the Gelling Agent</h4>
        <p>The ingredient list must specify the gelling agent. Vegan options use pectin, agar-agar, starch, or carrageenan. If you see "gelatin" anywhere in the list, the product contains animal collagen. There is no such thing as "plant-based gelatin."</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="eye" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>Scan for Hidden Animal Ingredients</h4>
        <p>Beeswax (glazing agent), carmine/cochineal/E120 (red color from insects), shellac/confectioner's glaze (insect secretion coating), and lanolin-derived ingredients are common non-vegan additives in candy that appears plant-based.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="shield" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>Look for Certifications</h4>
        <p>Certified Vegan logo, Vegan Society trademark, or PETA-Approved Vegan label require full supply chain auditing. These are the fastest way to verify a product without reading every ingredient. USDA Organic does not guarantee vegan status.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="warning" size={22} /></div>
        <h4>Beware of "Natural Flavors"</h4>
        <p>The term "natural flavors" can legally include animal-derived components. Some castoreum (from beaver glands) and other animal extracts qualify as "natural." Certified Vegan products have verified that their natural flavors are plant-sourced.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- VEGAN GUMMY BEARS VS WORMS -->
    <h2>Vegan Gummy Bears vs Vegan Gummy Worms: What Is the Difference?</h2>

    <p>Beyond shape, there are real differences between vegan gummy bears and vegan gummy worms that affect texture, flavor distribution, and even sweetness perception. Gummy bears have a more uniform flavor throughout because of their compact shape — every bite delivers the same taste. Gummy worms, being elongated, often feature two-tone flavors (sour coating + sweet interior) and a chewier texture due to the higher surface-area-to-volume ratio. For dedicated roundups, visit our <a href="/candy/vegan-gummy-bears/">vegan gummy bears</a> and <a href="/candy/vegan-gummy-worms/">vegan gummy worms</a> guides.</p>

