    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="faq-sec">
      <h2>Vegan Gummy Candy — Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details class="fq"><summary>What makes gummy candy vegan?</summary><p>Vegan gummy candy replaces animal-derived gelatin with plant-based gelling agents like pectin, agar-agar, or starch. It also excludes beeswax, carmine, shellac, and any other animal-derived ingredient. Most vegan gummies use natural fruit juices and plant-based colorants for flavor and color.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Does vegan gummy candy taste different from regular gummy candy?</summary><p>Modern pectin-based gummies are nearly indistinguishable from gelatin gummies in blind taste tests. The texture is slightly softer and less chewy, but premium brands like SmartSweets and Surf Sweets have formulations that most consumers prefer to traditional gelatin candy.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are SmartSweets gummy bears actually healthy?</summary><p>SmartSweets contain only 3g of sugar per bag versus 34g in traditional gummy bears. They are sweetened with allulose and stevia. They are a healthier candy alternative but are still candy — eat them as a treat, not a health food.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>What is the healthiest vegan gummy candy?</summary><p>SmartSweets leads in sugar reduction (3g/bag). YumEarth prioritizes organic, clean ingredients. For the healthiest overall profile — low sugar plus clean ingredients — SmartSweets offers the best macro profile. For ingredient purity, YumEarth and Surf Sweets win.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Is Haribo gummy candy vegan?</summary><p>No. Haribo gummy bears contain gelatin derived from animal collagen (typically pork) and beeswax as a glazing agent. Haribo does not currently offer a vegan-certified line in the US.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are vegan gummy candies gluten-free?</summary><p>Most vegan gummy candy is naturally gluten-free. SmartSweets, YumEarth, Surf Sweets, and Annie's are all certified gluten-free. Always check labels for cross-contamination warnings if you have celiac disease.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Where can I buy vegan gummy candy?</summary><p>Amazon, Whole Foods, Target, Walmart, Trader Joe's, and Sprouts all carry vegan gummy candy. Amazon has the widest selection and best multi-pack pricing.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>How can I tell if gummy candy contains gelatin?</summary><p>Check the ingredient list for "gelatin." Also look for beeswax, carmine (E120), and shellac (confectioner's glaze). Products using pectin, agar, or starch will list those as the gelling agent. Certified Vegan logos provide instant verification.</p></details>
    </section>

